.TH "qcom_scm_assign_mem" 9 "qcom_scm_assign_mem" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qcom_scm_assign_mem \- Make a secure call to reassign memory ownership
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qcom_scm_assign_mem
.BI "(phys_addr_t mem_addr "  ","
.BI "size_t mem_sz "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *srcvm "  ","
.BI "const struct qcom_scm_vmperm *newvm "  ","
.BI "unsigned int dest_cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mem_addr" 12
mem region whose ownership need to be reassigned
.IP "mem_sz" 12
size of the region.
.IP "srcvm" 12
vmid for current set of owners, each set bit in
flag indicate a unique owner
.IP "newvm" 12
array having new owners and corresponding permission
flags
.IP "dest_cnt" 12
number of owners in next set.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return negative errno on failure or 0 on success with \fIsrcvm\fP updated.
